# BiFoDe website (absent-altitude)

NGO site for **BiFoDe e.V.** — production **https://www.bifode.org** (Vercel). Full details: `AGENTS.md`.

## Stack & commands

- Astro 6, `@astrojs/vercel`, `output: 'server'`
- **Node 24** — `nvm use` (`.nvmrc`)
- Root: `npm run dev` → http://localhost:4321 · `npm run build` before merge · no lint/test script
- Rollup via `@rollup/wasm-node` (`package.json` overrides) — do not remove without reason

## Layout

- `src/pages/` — German routes; `src/pages/en/` — English mirror
- `src/content/{projekte,aktuelles,events}/` — collections (`src/content.config.ts`)
- `src/pages/api/contact.ts` — SMTP contact form
- `vercel.json` — bifode.de → www.bifode.org redirects only

## i18n

- DE at root (`/kontakt`, `/israel-community`, …); EN under `/en/`
- Update **both** locales when a page has a pair; formal nonprofit tone
- One language per page; `MainLayout` `lang`: `de` | `en`

## Content collections

| Collection | Key fields |
|------------|------------|
| `projekte` | `title`, `description` |
| `aktuelles` | `pubDate`, optional `draft` |
| `events` | ISO `start`/`end`, optional `titleEn`/`summaryEn`, `draft` |

## Env (never commit `.env`)

See `.env.example`: `SMTP_*`, `CONTACT_*`, `PUBLIC_JOTFORM_ANMELDUNG_URL`. Use `import.meta.env` in code.

## Workflow

- Minimal diffs; match neighboring files; no drive-by refactors
- **No git commit/push** unless the user asks
- **No new production deps** without confirmation
- Legal pages (`impressum`, `datenschutz`, cookie policies): change carefully

## Codex / agents

- Verify with `nvm use && npm run build` (1–2 min; Vercel bundling may pause ~60s)
- Codex: run build **outside sandbox** if it hangs; use Node 24, not only Codex.app Node for installs
